# PaddleOCR Project Core Rules

## Communication
- Respond in Simplified Chinese.
- Keep answers concise and actionable.

## Git Workflow
- Commit after finishing each requested change set.
- Never push unless the user explicitly requests push.

## Runtime and Deployment
- Windows runtime uses `uvicorn`; do not rely on `gunicorn` on Windows.
- Keep model default paths under `offline_bundle/models/*`.
- Keep offline deployment assets under `offline_bundle/`.

## API Contract
- Keep OCR response structure unified: `success`, `traceId`, `elapsedMs`, `data`.
- Keep `data.fields` as required output, with empty `value` fallback for missing fields.

## Safety
- Do not remove user test data under `test/data`.
- Do not commit secrets or credentials.
